ORLANDO Pirates and Mamelodi Sundowns, arguably the two biggest team remaining in the Nedbank Cup, have avoided each other in the Last 16 draw which took place at MultiChoice headquarters in Randburg on Monday. Sundowns, who will be looking to complete a domestic treble by winning the Ke Yona Cup in addition to the MTN 8 and the DStv Premiership, were draw against the lowly Mathaithai FC in a David v Goliath affair. Pirates on the other hand, eager to stop Downs from completing a clean sweep domestically, will have to go through defending champions Marumo Gallants.In an all-top-flight affair, Swallows FC will lock horns against Royal AM. Another exciting encounter between two top-flight teams will see 2019 champions TS Galaxy face Baroka FC. Galaxy dumped Kaizer Chiefs out of the Ke Yona Cup for the second time having embarrassed the Soweto giants in the final in 2019 where they became the first team from the second division to win the competition. Nedbank Cup Last-16 draw Venda Football Academy vs University of Pretoria Swallows FC vs Royal AM Marumo Gallants vs Orlando Pirates Platinum City Rovers vs SuperSport United TS Galaxy vs Baroka FC Sinenkani FC vs Tshakhuma FC Summerfield Dynamos vs Black Eagles Mamelodi Sundowns vs Mathaithai FC